When the park closed , the sole steam locomotive at the time was sold to the Pacific Coast Railroad in Santa Margarita , California , where it now operates .
However , several years before , presumably , the other steam locomotive was sold to a private collector in Durango , Colorado .
The diesel went to Six Flags America and operates there .
The steam outline locomotive " Elizabeth " ( formerly from Opryland ) went to Six Flags Over Georgia where it is currently stored .
