align =
centerUSA REFERENCES IN OTHER SIX FLAGS PROPERTIES Section::::References in other Six Flags properties .
The 2008 video game Six Flags Fun Park features an area named " Astro City " , with space - themed attractions .
IN POPULAR
CULTURE TRAVIS
SCOTT Section::::In popular culture .
Section::::Travis Scott .
Rapper Travis Scott was born and raised in Houston .
He announced that his third studio album would be titled Astroworld , in homage of his hometown Houston .
In an XXL Magazine interview , Travis talked about when Astroworld was closed and demolished , saying " They took AstroWorld away from us in Houston " .
In that interview , one of Travis ' friends said that " Someone said they took it away to make the rodeo bigger " which is , non - coincidentally , the title of his debut album , Rodeo .
Astroworld was released on August 3 , 2018 .
JURASSIC PARK Section::::Jurassic Park .
In the novel Jurassic Park , park engineer Ray Arnold thinks about all of his contributions to the technological world including Walt Disney World , Six Flags Magic Mountain , and Astroworld in Houston .
